description: This is a ready-to-fish gillnetter, which is set up for Puget Sound but could also fish any area in Alaska as well. It is moored at Friday Harbor right now, but will be hauled out in Bellingham in March. A permit lease can be arranged if needed. F/V Satisfaction 32'x11.5'x2.5' Fiberglass hull (with tunnel) built by Uniflite in 1980. This boat was built for Bristol Bay but instead fished Puget Sound. The bowthruster was installed 2007. 300 hp diesel Cummins 555 with Twin Disc 506 gear. Very reliable and burns 5 gph at 8kts. Keel cooled so there is not raw water interaction between the sea and the engine, and you can run the engine no problem when it is hauled out. Hydraulic 8-inch Bowthruster with controls at all three stations. This bowthruster has gotten me out of any tangle I managed to get myself into! Works great. Hatches will hold 10k pounds, but 6k organized in brailers. There is an insulated watertight brailer for the center hatch, and two slush bags (one on each side), plus brailers. Hydraulics are very strong, and the bulletproof Easthope drum drive has a high and low speed so it can really crank it in when it needs to pull. Levelwind works great with no quirks, and the sternroller can power in and out, if desired. Mast and boom with 2,000-pound electric winch. Electronics include GPS, VHF, radar, 2 sounders and AC shore power w/ battery charger. Galley is comfortable with a big table and a Dickinson "Bristol" oil stove. Running water and a sink. Two bunks down below, plus a head; there is a holding tank (but it has never been used) or a direct overboard. This is a great fishing boat that maneuvers very well and handles the sea just fine. The low price is because the engine is tired and the back deck could use an overhaul. I would have kept fishing this boat but I just bought a larger and faster boat that will better suit my needs (I process much of my own catch). Thank you for your interest
title: 32' Gillnetter w bowthruster, mast & boom

description: Boat Slip 44ft at Semiahmoo near Blaine Washington. This is a very beautiful, secure, friendly well run and well maintained marina. Wide docks, picnic area, small store with some marine parts, snacks, lunch bar and soft drinks as well as wine and beer. Lots of free parking. All manner of sea birds and eagles populate Drayton Harbor and surrounding areas. Semiahmoo Spit has a black topped walking path with little traffic and right along the beach. Modern clean showers, Wifi and just a few minutes walk to Semiahmoo Resort and Spa. There is a lively community of boaters here, with activities such as Friday night barbeques and music in the summer. Semiahmoo has the cheapest fuel rates of all the local marinas. You also save fuel by being close to the San Juan and Canadian Gulf Islands. If you like fishing, Boundary Bay and Pt Whitehorn are just a few miles away. A short dingy ride gets you to White Rock B.C. with many restaurants and great night life. Semiahmoo is only 8 minutes from I-5 and all this for $45 a month less than Blaine or Squalicum Harbors and hundreds less than Vancouver B.C. We are looking for a long term lease. The slip number is C-16 and is close to the ramp, easy in and out of the slip. Prevailing winds set you off the dock. This is a link to more information about Semiahmoo Marina http://semiahmoomarina.com/our-community/around-the-marina-photo-gallery December Special - sign up before 31 Dec and receive 30% off, until 31 March 2017. PH show contact info

description: 35' Bristol NW Trawler built by Albert Jensen & Sons - Best Offer Own a piece of NW history. This meticulously cared-for cruiser creates double-takes wherever she goes.
